  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Peter
      content: "  This letter is from Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ.I am writing
        to God\u2019s chosen people who are living as foreigners in the provinces
        of Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: <b>Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, </b>and <b>Bithynia </b>were
          Roman provinces in what is now Turkey.
    - title: The Hope of Eternal Life
      content: 'God the Father knew you and chose you long ago, and his Spirit has
        made you holy. As a result, you have obeyed him and have been cleansed by
        the blood of Jesus Christ.May God give you more and more grace and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All praise to God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ. It is by
        his great mercy that we have been born again, because God raised Jesus Christ
        from the dead. Now we live with great expectation, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and we have a priceless inheritance\u2014an inheritance that is kept
        in heaven for you, pure and undefiled, beyond the reach of change and decay. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And through your faith, God is protecting you by his power until
        you receive this salvation, which is ready to be revealed on the last day
        for all to see.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So be truly glad.[[COMMENT(0)]] There is wonderful joy ahead, even
        though you must endure many trials for a little while. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: Or <b>So you are truly glad.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "These trials will show that your faith is genuine. It is being tested
        as fire tests and purifies gold\u2014though your faith is far more precious
        than mere gold. So when your faith remains strong through many trials, it
        will bring you much praise and glory and honor on the day when Jesus Christ
        is revealed to the whole world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You love him even though you have never seen him. Though you do not
        see him now, you trust him; and you rejoice with a glorious, inexpressible
        joy. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The reward for trusting him will be the salvation of your souls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This salvation was something even the prophets wanted to know more
        about when they prophesied about this gracious salvation prepared for you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They wondered what time or situation the Spirit of Christ within
        them was talking about when he told them in advance about Christ\u2019s suffering
        and his great glory afterward.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Call to Holy Living
      content: 'They were told that their messages were not for themselves, but for
        you. And now this Good News has been announced to you by those who preached
        in the power of the Holy Spirit sent from heaven. It is all so wonderful
        that even the angels are eagerly watching these things happen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So prepare your minds for action and exercise self-control. Put all
        your hope in the gracious salvation that will come to you when Jesus Christ
        is revealed to the world. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So you must live as God\u2019s obedient children. Don\u2019t slip
        back into your old ways of living to satisfy your own desires. You didn\u2019t
        know any better then. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now you must be holy in everything you do, just as God who chose
        you is holy. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Scriptures say, \u201CYou must be holy because I am holy.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:16 '
        content: Lev 11:44-45; 19:2; 20:7.
    - title: 
      content: "And remember that the heavenly Father to whom you pray has no favorites.
        He will judge or reward you according to what you do. So you must live in
        reverent fear of him during your time here as \u201Ctemporary residents.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you know that God paid a ransom to save you from the empty life
        you inherited from your ancestors. And it was not paid with mere gold or
        silver, which lose their value. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It was the precious blood of Christ, the sinless, spotless Lamb of
        God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God chose him as your ransom long before the world began, but now
        in these last days he has been revealed for your sake.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Through Christ you have come to trust in God. And you have placed
        your faith and hope in God because he raised Christ from the dead and gave
        him great glory.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You were cleansed from your sins when you obeyed the truth, so now
        you must show sincere love to each other as brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Love each other deeply with all your heart.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:22a '
        content: Greek <b>must have brotherly love.</b>
      - number: '1:22b '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>with a pure heart.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For you have been born again, but not to a life that will quickly
        end. Your new life will last forever because it comes from the eternal, living
        word of God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As the Scriptures say,\u201CPeople are like grass;their beauty is
        like a flower in the field.The grass withers and the flower fades.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  So get rid of all evil behavior. Be done with all deceit, hypocrisy,
        jealousy, and all unkind speech. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like newborn babies, you must crave pure spiritual milk so that you
        will grow into a full experience of salvation. Cry out for this nourishment, '
      comments: []
    - title: "Living Stones for God\u2019s House"
      content: "now that you have had a taste of the Lord\u2019s kindness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You are coming to Christ, who is the living cornerstone of God\u2019s
        temple. He was rejected by people, but he was chosen by God for great honor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you are living stones that God is building into his spiritual
        temple. What\u2019s more, you are his holy priests.[[COMMENT(0)]] Through
        the mediation of Jesus Christ, you offer spiritual sacrifices that please
        God. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:5 '
        content: Greek <b>holy priesthood</b>.
    - title: 
      content: "As the Scriptures say,\u201CI am placing a cornerstone in Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]chosen
        for great honor,and anyone who trusts in himwill never be disgraced.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6a '
        content: Greek <b>in Zion.</b>
      - number: '2:6b '
        content: Isa 28:16 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, you who trust him recognize the honor God has given him.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        But for those who reject him,\u201CThe stone that the builders rejectedhas
        now become the cornerstone.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:7a '
        content: Or <b>Yes, for you who believe, there is honor.</b>
      - number: '2:7b '
        content: Ps 118:22.
    - title: 
      content: "And,\u201CHe is the stone that makes people stumble,the rock that
        makes them fall.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]They stumble because they do not obey
        God\u2019s word, and so they meet the fate that was planned for them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        content: Isa 8:14.
    - title: 
      content: "But you are not like that, for you are a chosen people. You are royal
        priests,[[COMMENT(0)]] a holy nation, God\u2019s very own possession. As
        a result, you can show others the goodness of God, for he called you out
        of the darkness into his wonderful light.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:9 '
        content: Greek <b>a royal priesthood.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COnce you had no identity as a people;now you are God\u2019s
        people.Once you received no mercy;now you have received God\u2019s mercy.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        content: Hos 1:6, 9; 2:23.
    - title: 
      content: "Dear friends, I warn you as \u201Ctemporary residents and foreigners\u201D
        to keep away from worldly desires that wage war against your very souls. "
      comments: []
    - title: Respecting People in Authority
      content: 'Be careful to live properly among your unbelieving neighbors. Then
        even if they accuse you of doing wrong, they will see your honorable behavior,
        and they will give honor to God when he judges the world.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:12 '
        content: Or <b>on the day of visitation.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For the Lord\u2019s sake, submit to all human authority\u2014whether
        the king as head of state, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'or the officials he has appointed. For the king has sent them to
        punish those who do wrong and to honor those who do right.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It is God\u2019s will that your honorable lives should silence those
        ignorant people who make foolish accusations against you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For you are free, yet you are God\u2019s slaves, so don\u2019t use
        your freedom as an excuse to do evil. "
      comments: []
    - title: Slaves
      content: 'Respect everyone, and love the family of believers.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Fear God, and respect the king.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        content: Greek <b>love the brotherhood.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "You who are slaves must submit to your masters with all respect.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Do what they tell you\u2014not only if they are kind and reasonable, but
        even if they are cruel. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: Or <b>because you fear God; </b>Greek reads <b>in all fear.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For God is pleased when, conscious of his will, you patiently endure
        unjust treatment. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Of course, you get no credit for being patient if you are beaten
        for doing wrong. But if you suffer for doing good and endure it patiently,
        God is pleased with you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God called you to do good, even if it means suffering, just as
        Christ suffered[[COMMENT(0)]] for you. He is your example, and you must follow
        in his steps.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:21 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>died.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He never sinned,nor ever deceived anyone.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:22 '
        content: Isa 53:9.
    - title: 
      content: 'He did not retaliate when he was insulted,nor threaten revenge when
        he suffered.He left his case in the hands of God,who always judges fairly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He personally carried our sinsin his body on the crossso that we
        can be dead to sinand live for what is right.By his woundsyou are healed.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Wives
      content: '  In the same way, you wives must accept the authority of your husbands.
        Then, even if some refuse to obey the Good News, your godly lives will speak
        to them without any words. They will be won over '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'by observing your pure and reverent lives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be concerned about the outward beauty of fancy hairstyles,
        expensive jewelry, or beautiful clothes. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You should clothe yourselves instead with the beauty that comes from
        within, the unfading beauty of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is so precious
        to God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is how the holy women of old made themselves beautiful. They
        put their trust in God and accepted the authority of their husbands. '
      comments: []
    - title: Husbands
      content: 'For instance, Sarah obeyed her husband, Abraham, and called him her
        master. You are her daughters when you do what is right without fear of what
        your husbands might do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: All Christians
      content: "In the same way, you husbands must give honor to your wives. Treat
        your wife with understanding as you live together. She may be weaker than
        you are, but she is your equal partner in God\u2019s gift of new life. Treat
        her as you should so your prayers will not be hindered.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Finally, all of you should be of one mind. Sympathize with each other.
        Love each other as brothers and sisters.[[COMMENT(0)]] Be tenderhearted,
        and keep a humble attitude. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: Greek <b>Show brotherly love.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t repay evil for evil. Don\u2019t retaliate with insults
        when people insult you. Instead, pay them back with a blessing. That is what
        God has called you to do, and he will grant you his blessing. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Scriptures say,\u201CIf you want to enjoy lifeand see many
        happy days,keep your tongue from speaking eviland your lips from telling
        lies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Turn away from evil and do good.Search for peace, and work to maintain
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Suffering for Doing Good
      content: "The eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> watch over those who
        do right,and his ears are open to their prayers.But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        turns his faceagainst those who do evil.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:10-12 '
        content: Ps 34:12-16.
    - title: 
      content: 'Now, who will want to harm you if you are eager to do good? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But even if you suffer for doing what is right, God will reward you
        for it. So don\u2019t worry or be afraid of their threats. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, you must worship Christ as Lord of your life. And if someone
        asks about your hope as a believer, always be ready to explain it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But do this in a gentle and respectful way.[[COMMENT(0)]] Keep your
        conscience clear. Then if people speak against you, they will be ashamed
        when they see what a good life you live because you belong to Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: Some English translations put this sentence in verse 15.
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember, it is better to suffer for doing good, if that is what
        God wants, than to suffer for doing wrong!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Christ suffered[[COMMENT(0)]] for our sins once for all time. He
        never sinned, but he died for sinners to bring you safely home to God. He
        suffered physical death, but he was raised to life in the Spirit.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:18a '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>died.</b>
      - number: '3:18b '
        content: Or <b>in spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "So he went and preached to the spirits in prison\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'those who disobeyed God long ago when God waited patiently while
        Noah was building his boat. Only eight people were saved from drowning in
        that terrible flood.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:20 '
        content: Greek <b>saved through water.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And that water is a picture of baptism, which now saves you, not
        by removing dirt from your body, but as a response to God from[[COMMENT(0)]]
        a clean conscience. It is effective because of the resurrection of Jesus
        Christ.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:21 '
        content: Or <b>as an appeal to God for.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: Living for God
      content: '  So then, since Christ suffered physical pain, you must arm yourselves
        with the same attitude he had, and be ready to suffer, too. For if you have
        suffered physically for Christ, you have finished with sin.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Or <b>For the one </b>[or <b>One</b>] <b>who has suffered physically
          has finished with sin.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "You won\u2019t spend the rest of your lives chasing your own desires,
        but you will be anxious to do the will of God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have had enough in the past of the evil things that godless people
        enjoy\u2014their immorality and lust, their feasting and drunkenness and
        wild parties, and their terrible worship of idols.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Of course, your former friends are surprised when you no longer plunge
        into the flood of wild and destructive things they do. So they slander you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But remember that they will have to face God, who stands ready to
        judge everyone, both the living and the dead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the Good News was preached to those who are now dead[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014so
        although they were destined to die like all people,[[COMMENT(1)]] they now
        live forever with God in the Spirit.[[COMMENT(2)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:6a '
        content: Greek <b>preached even to the dead.</b>
      - number: '4:6b '
        content: Or <b>so although people had judged them worthy of death.</b>
      - number: '4:6c '
        content: Or <b>in spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The end of the world is coming soon. Therefore, be earnest and disciplined
        in your prayers. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Most important of all, continue to show deep love for each other,
        for love covers a multitude of sins. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Cheerfully share your home with those who need a meal or a place
        to stay.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God has given each of you a gift from his great variety of spiritual
        gifts. Use them well to serve one another. '
      comments: []
    - title: Suffering for Being a Christian
      content: 'Do you have the gift of speaking? Then speak as though God himself
        were speaking through you. Do you have the gift of helping others? Do it
        with all the strength and energy that God supplies. Then everything you do
        will bring glory to God through Jesus Christ. All glory and power to him
        forever and ever! Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Dear friends, don\u2019t be surprised at the fiery trials you are
        going through, as if something strange were happening to you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, be very glad\u2014for these trials make you partners with
        Christ in his suffering, so that you will have the wonderful joy of seeing
        his glory when it is revealed to all the world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you are insulted because you bear the name of Christ, you will
        be blessed, for the glorious Spirit of God[[COMMENT(0)]] rests upon you.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:14a '
        content: Or <b>for the glory of God, which is his Spirit.</b>
      - number: '4:14b '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>On their part he is blasphemed, but on your
          part he is glorified.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "If you suffer, however, it must not be for murder, stealing, making
        trouble, or prying into other people\u2019s affairs. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But it is no shame to suffer for being a Christian. Praise God for
        the privilege of being called by his name! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the time has come for judgment, and it must begin with God\u2019s
        household. And if judgment begins with us, what terrible fate awaits those
        who have never obeyed God\u2019s Good News? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And also,\u201CIf the righteous are barely saved,what will happen
        to godless sinners?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:18 '
        content: Prov 11:31 (Greek version).
  - verses:
    - title: Advice for Elders and Young Men
      content: '  And now, a word to you who are elders in the churches. I, too,
        am an elder and a witness to the sufferings of Christ. And I, too, will share
        in his glory when he is revealed to the whole world. As a fellow elder, I
        appeal to you: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Care for the flock that God has entrusted to you. Watch over it willingly,
        not grudgingly\u2014not for what you will get out of it, but because you
        are eager to serve God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t lord it over the people assigned to your care, but lead
        them by your own good example. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when the Great Shepherd appears, you will receive a crown of
        never-ending glory and honor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the same way, you who are younger must accept the authority of
        the elders. And all of you, dress yourselves in humility as you relate to
        one another, for\u201CGod opposes the proudbut gives grace to the humble.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: Prov 3:34 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'So humble yourselves under the mighty power of God, and at the right
        time he will lift you up in honor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give all your worries and cares to God, for he cares about you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Stay alert! Watch out for your great enemy, the devil. He prowls
        around like a roaring lion, looking for someone to devour. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Stand firm against him, and be strong in your faith. Remember that
        your family of believers[[COMMENT(0)]] all over the world is going through
        the same kind of suffering you are.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:9 '
        content: Greek <b>your brotherhood.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'In his kindness God called you to share in his eternal glory by means
        of Christ Jesus. So after you have suffered a little while, he will restore,
        support, and strengthen you, and he will place you on a firm foundation. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Peter\u2019s Final Greetings"
      content: 'All power to him forever! Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have written and sent this short letter to you with the help of
        Silas,[[COMMENT(0)]] whom I commend to you as a faithful brother. My purpose
        in writing is to encourage you and assure you that what you are experiencing
        is truly part of God\u2019s grace for you. Stand firm in this grace.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:12 '
        content: Greek <b>Silvanus.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Your sister church here in Babylon[[COMMENT(0)]] sends you greetings,
        and so does my son Mark. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:13 '
        content: Greek <b>The elect one in Babylon. </b>Babylon was probably symbolic
          for Rome.
